xX25ChannelIndex.name: xX25ChannelIndex
xX25ChannelIndex.description: The ifIndex value for the X.25 physical link.

xX25ChannelLowPVC.name: xX25ChannelLowPVC
xX25ChannelLowPVC.description: Lowest PVC channel. Setting it to zero indicates 'none', and will also set the xX25ChannelHighPVC to zero. If set to a non-zero value and xX25ChannelHighPVC is zero, xX25ChannelHighPVC will be set to the same value. Otherwise, xX25ChannelLowPVC must be less than or equal to xX25ChannelHighPVC.

xX25ChannelHighPVC.name: xX25ChannelHighPVC
xX25ChannelHighPVC.description: Highest PVC channel. Setting it to 0 indicates none, and will also set the xX25ChannelLowPVC to 0. If set to a non-zero value and xX25ChannelLowPVC is zero, xX25ChannelLowPVC will be set to the same value. Otherwise, xX25ChannelHighPVC must be less than or equal to xX25ChannelLowPVC.

xX25ChannelNetwork.name: xX25ChannelNetwork
xX25ChannelNetwork.description: The type of network being run.

xX25ChannelMaxPrecedence.name: xX25ChannelMaxPrecedence
xX25ChannelMaxPrecedence.description: The maximum level of IP precedence supported.

xX25ChannelStdVersion.name: xX25ChannelStdVersion
xX25ChannelStdVersion.description: The standard year supported by x25. Values are usually 1980 or 1984 (the default).

xX25VcCfgTable.name: xX25VcCfgTable
xX25VcCfgTable.description: These objects contain information about the virtual circuit configuration in an X.25 PLE. These values are the configured values for circuits that may or may not be connected. Unconfigured calls may be added to this table as calls are accepted.

xX25VcCfgIndex.name: xX25VcCfgIndex
xX25VcCfgIndex.description: An arbitrary index value for the virtual circuit.

xX25VcCfgInterfaceIndex.name: xX25VcCfgInterfaceIndex
xX25VcCfgInterfaceIndex.description: ifIndex of ITouch logical interface associated with this VC.

xX25VcCfgLinkIndex.name: xX25VcCfgLinkIndex
xX25VcCfgLinkIndex.description: ifIndex of physical link on which this VC resides.

xX25VcCfgProtocol.name: xX25VcCfgProtocol
xX25VcCfgProtocol.description: Protocol which is being encapsulated by this VC.

xX25VcCfgEncapsulation.name: xX25VcCfgEncapsulation
xX25VcCfgEncapsulation.description: Encapsulation method used by this VC.

xX25VcCfgPvc.name: xX25VcCfgPvc
xX25VcCfgPvc.description: Channel number if VC is a PVC, else 0. The value must be in the range of xX25ChannelLowPVC to xX25ChannelHighPVC

xX25VcCfgPartnerIpAddress.name: xX25VcCfgPartnerIpAddress
xX25VcCfgPartnerIpAddress.description: IP address of the partner over this VC. This must be configured if IP packets will not be MAC-encapsulated.

xX25VcCfgClearFacilities.name: xX25VcCfgClearFacilities
xX25VcCfgClearFacilities.description: Control to clear the VC call facilities string. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes the string to be cleared.

xX25VcCfgStatus.name: xX25VcCfgStatus
xX25VcCfgStatus.description: Setting to 'invalid' removes this VC from the table. If 'valid', setting to 'valid' has no effect, otherwise it creates an entry.

xX25LinkTable.name: xX25LinkTable
xX25LinkTable.description: These objects contain information about the configuration of the X.25 physical links necessary for the ITouch Bridge/Router. Unless otherwise noted, changes to these objects require that the X.25 physical link be restarted in order for the changes to take effect.

xX25LinkIndex.name: xX25LinkIndex
xX25LinkIndex.description: The ifIndex value for a ITouch physical link.

xX25LinkRRDelay.name: xX25LinkRRDelay
xX25LinkRRDelay.description: Number of packets received before an RR will be sent. The value must be less than the xX25CallParmInWindowSize. Modifying this object does not require the X.25 physical link to be restarted. 0 indicates that RR will not be sent.

xX25LinkIdleTimeout.name: xX25LinkIdleTimeout
xX25LinkIdleTimeout.description: Length of time in minutes that a virtual circuit may be idle before the circuit will be cleared. Modifying this object does not require the X.25 physical link to be restarted.

xX25LinkHoldDownTimer.name: xX25LinkHoldDownTimer
xX25LinkHoldDownTimer.description: Length of time in minutes after a virtual circuit has been cleared before it may make a call again. Modifying this object does not require the X.25 physical link to be restarted.

xX25LinkAccUncfgCalls.name: xX25LinkAccUncfgCalls
xX25LinkAccUncfgCalls.description: Indicates whether unconfigured, non-reverse charged calls will be accepted. Modifying this object does not require the X.25 physical link to be restarted.

xX25LinkDefWindSize.name: xX25LinkDefWindSize
xX25LinkDefWindSize.description: Default packet level window size for this link.

xX25LinkMaxWindSize.name: xX25LinkMaxWindSize
xX25LinkMaxWindSize.description: Maximum packet level window size for this link.

xX25LinkDefPktSize.name: xX25LinkDefPktSize
xX25LinkDefPktSize.description: Default packet size for this link.

xX25LinkDefThrptClassIn.name: xX25LinkDefThrptClassIn
xX25LinkDefThrptClassIn.description: Default input throughput class for this link.

xX25LinkDefThrptClassOut.name: xX25LinkDefThrptClassOut
xX25LinkDefThrptClassOut.description: Default output throughput class for this link.

xX25LinkDefThrptClassInMsk.name: xX25LinkDefThrptClassInMsk
xX25LinkDefThrptClassInMsk.description: Default incoming throughput class mask for this link.

xX25LinkDefThrptClassOutMsk.name: xX25LinkDefThrptClassOutMsk
xX25LinkDefThrptClassOutMsk.description: Default outgoing throughput class mask for this link.

xX25LinkFlowCtrlNeg.name: xX25LinkFlowCtrlNeg
xX25LinkFlowCtrlNeg.description: Indicates whether flow control negotiation will be performed on this link.

xX25LinkThrptClassNeg.name: xX25LinkThrptClassNeg
xX25LinkThrptClassNeg.description: Indicates whether throughput class negotiation will be performed on this link.

xX25LinkICallBarred.name: xX25LinkICallBarred
xX25LinkICallBarred.description: Indicates whether incoming calls are barred on this link.

xX25LinkOCallBarred.name: xX25LinkOCallBarred
xX25LinkOCallBarred.description: Indicates whether outgoing calls are barred on this link.

xX25LinkOneOut.name: xX25LinkOneOut
xX25LinkOneOut.description: Indicates whether the link supports one way outgoing channels.

xX25LinkOneIn.name: xX25LinkOneIn
xX25LinkOneIn.description: Indicates whether the link supports one way incoming channels.

xX25LinkRevChargeAcc.name: xX25LinkRevChargeAcc
xX25LinkRevChargeAcc.description: Indicates whether reverse charge acceptance may be configured on this link.

xX25LinkLocalChargePrevent.name: xX25LinkLocalChargePrevent
xX25LinkLocalChargePrevent.description: Indicates whether local charge prevention may be configured on the link.

xX25LinkRpoa.name: xX25LinkRpoa
xX25LinkRpoa.description: Indicates whether RPOA may be configured on the link.

xX25LinkNui.name: xX25LinkNui
xX25LinkNui.description: Indicates whether NUI may be configured on the link.

xX25LinkMaxPacketSize.name: xX25LinkMaxPacketSize
xX25LinkMaxPacketSize.description: Maximum size of packets on the link.

xX25LinkInsertCallingAddr.name: xX25LinkInsertCallingAddr
xX25LinkInsertCallingAddr.description: Indicates whether the caller's X.121 address should be inserted into the the call request packet.

xX25LinkDefaultInterface.name: xX25LinkDefaultInterface
xX25LinkDefaultInterface.description: The ITouch logical ifIndex to which new SVCs should be attached, when 'accept unconfigured calls' is enabled. A value of zero means 'create a new interface'.
